'''Sri Lankans in France''' refer to residents and citizens of [[Sri Lankan]] ancestry, who were born in or immigrated to [[France]] legally and illegally. The estimated population of Sri Lankans in France is from 120,000 - 150,000.

==History==
Since the [[Sri Lankan Civil War]] the issue of illegal Sri Lankan immigration is a topic of concern for France.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sri Lanka|url=http://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/en/country-files_156/sri-lanka_505/index.html|work=Political relations|publisher=French Ministry of Foreign and European Affairs|accessdate=28 June 2011}}</ref> 

==Demographics==
The Sri Lankan population in France is estimated at approximately 120,000<ref>{{cite web|title=Sri Lanka-France relations|url=http://www.srilankaembassy.fr/?Sri_Lanka-France_relations|work=Sri Lankan community in France|publisher=Embassy of Sri Lanka in France|accessdate=28 June 2011}}</ref> - 150,000<ref>{{cite book|title=BASUG Remittance workshop for Sri Lankan Diaspora in Paris=http://www.basug.nl/uploads/files/20100710_Report%20BASUG-JMDI%20Workshop,%20Paris.pdf}}</ref>

==Organizations==
The Sri Lankan Diaspora have created a number of associations which organise Sri Lankan festivals, cultural functions and sports events for the Sri Lankan community.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sri Lanka-France relations|url=http://www.srilankaembassy.fr/?Sri_Lanka-France_relations|work=Sri Lankan community in France|publisher=Embassy of Sri Lanka in France|accessdate=28 June 2011}}</ref> 

==Notable people==
* [[Tampalawela Dhammaratana]] - French Buddhist monk

